Lab: High-Level Logic Vulnerability

Description

The application contains a business logic flaw that allows users to manipulate the intended workflow and obtain an unintended outcome.

---

Objective

Exploit the application's business logic to purchase an item at a lower price than intended.

---

Vulnerability

Business Logic Vulnerability

---

Steps

Step 1: Login

Login using the provided credentials.

Step 2: Browse Products

Navigate to the shop and add an expensive item to the cart.

Step 3: Observe Requests

Intercept requests using Burp Suite and identify:

POST /cart
POST /cart/checkout

Step 4: Analyze Workflow

Observe how the application calculates pricing and discounts.

Step 5: Manipulate Logic

Modify the workflow to apply discounts repeatedly or in an unintended sequence.

Step 6: Checkout

Proceed with checkout and verify that the product is purchased at an unintended price.

---

Impact

Users can abuse business rules to obtain products below their intended cost.

---

Root Cause

The application trusts workflow assumptions instead of validating business rules on the server side.

---

Remediation

- Validate pricing server-side.
- Prevent repeated discount application.
- Recalculate final prices before checkout.

---

Key Takeaway

Business logic vulnerabilities occur when applications assume users will follow the intended workflow instead of enforcing rules on the backend.